  "title": "Daily Report - 2026-04-19",
  "categories": [
    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Discord Community Discussion - April 19, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "A user asked whether there is any way to stake ElizaOS tokens. Multiple community members, including DorianD and Odilitime, confirmed that staking is currently not available for ElizaOS.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241"
        },
        {
          "text": "Community member satsbased shared tweets from shawmakesmagic explaining the background behind the ai16z token migration. According to the posts, the migration was forced because the original platform refused to implement voting features, was uncooperative in private communications, and dumped 5 percent of the token supply on holders, ultimately causing significant harm to the project.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "images": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/embed-image-1495531069569761383_4a76052f.jpg"
        },
        {
          "text": "A scam alert was raised in the community after a user reported suspicious airdrop activity in the arena channel, apparently shared by someone impersonating a known community member named kenk. Moderators confirmed it was a scam, warned users not to click any links, banned the impersonating accounts, and confirmed the scammers were nuked and banned.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1776648308134-l6xgri.png"
        },
        {
          "text": "A developer posted in the coders channel seeking 1 to 2 project collaborations. They described experience across full-stack development using React, Next.js, Node, Python, and cloud infrastructure, blockchain development including Solidity and Rust for Solana, and AI and machine learning work involving LangChain, OpenAI APIs, vector databases, and RAG pipelines. Notable past projects include an AI trade executor that reduced MEV risk by approximately 40 percent, a generative NFT collection that sold out in 22 minutes, and a cross-chain portfolio tracker using OpenAI to summarize risk. The developer invited anyone with a project to reach out via direct message.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1300025221834739744",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1776648329984-jkvinq.jpg"
        }
      ],
      "topic": "discordrawdata"
    },
    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Development Summary: April 19, 2026",
      "content": {
        "text": "Development on April 19, 2026 centered on strengthening agent infrastructure through memory and orchestration improvements, while also expanding the plugin ecosystem. On the orchestration and memory side, subagent synthesis was refined by implementing end_turn reading and removing the task-heartbeat module. The InMemoryDatabaseAdapter was improved to handle accurate memory updates when roomId changes occur. Discord routing and submodule dependencies were also updated for the plugin-agent-orchestrator and plugin-cron components. A new plugin called plugin-hiveexchange was introduced to enable agent-native prediction markets. In the plugin registry, two additional plugins are pending addition: elizaos-plugin-deepblue and plugin-elizaos. New discussions have also emerged around integrating Merxex to facilitate commerce between autonomous agents, with two related proposals submitted as open issues.",
        "sources": "https://elizaos.github.io/api/summaries/overall/day/2026-04-19.json",
        "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1776648382750-zsili.png"
      },
      "topic": "miscellaneous"
    }
